FBIS4-40951 "drsov119_b_94023" FBIS-SOV-94-119 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Zhirinovskiy Expresses Support Zhirinovskiy Expresses Support LD2106135394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1347 GMT 21 Jun 94 LD2106135394 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yuriy Shcherban] [Text] Moscow June 21 TASS -- Russian nationalist leader Vladimir Zhirinovskiy expressed today his solidarity with Valentin Varennikov, a leader of the 1991 abortive Soviet coup, who is now at trial by the military panel of the Supreme Court. Varennikov was the only ringleader of the attempted coup who refused to accept parliament's amnesty in February and insisted that a court investigation of his case goes on. Zhirinovskiy appeared in the court-room on Tuesday to make a joint statement with Varennikov saying that a special perliamentary commission should control the general prosecutor's office investigating the case.
